AB  - This research presents a model that combines knowledge graphs with deep neural networks to achieve quality prediction in tobacco production. In particular, a neural network model integrating a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and a Bidirectional Gated Recurrent Unit (BiGRU) is designed to predict key quality indicators in the cut-tobacco drying process, such as the temperature of the drying cylinder wall. The experimental results demonstrate that this model exhibits superiority in predicting the quality of the tobacco, offering corresponding guidance of tobacco production. Keywords: tobacco, deep learning, intelligent prediction, knowledge graph
