TI  - Evaluation of drying kinetics models and functional properties of Etlingera linguiformis (Roxb.) RMSm.: An aromatic ginger from North East India
T2  - INDUSTRIAL CROPS AND PRODUCTS
M3  - Article
AB  - The food industry faces challenges in preserving the quality of different processed, fruits, vegetables, spices etc. Etlingera linguiformis is an underutilized spice commonly, known as aromatic ginger, available in Northeast India, whose rhizome has gained, attention for its diverse health-promoting properties. This study assessed the rhizomes, subjected to various drying methods to understand the drying kinetic models and other, functional properties like essential oil yield, chemical profiling, physicochemical, properties, sensory attributes, scavenging activity, and cytotoxicity. Results revealed, that electric drying (ED) at 60 degrees C with least drying period consist diverse volatile, compounds, enhancing antioxidant activity, sensory attributes, and highest cell, viability. However, sun drying (SD), shade drying (SHD), and hot air oven drying (OD), require longer drying times. Additionally, the study examined seven different drying models and among them the Midilli model identified as most suitable for characterizing, the drying kinetics of the sliced rhizome of E. linguiformis based on the maximum R2, value. GC-MS investigation indicated that estragole (86.92-100 %) and methyleugenol (1.31-6.84 %) are the predominant volatile components in both fresh rhizomes and, those subjected to various drying methods. To maintain the quality of the rhizome, ED, at 60 degrees C emerged as promising drying conditions, ensuring the preservation of appearance, biological activities, and sensory aspects. It achieves the highest scavenging activity among all tested concentrations, with an EC50 of 58.03 mu g/ml. This, strong antioxidant effect is likely due to its high monoterpene content, particularly, estragole. Additionally, this drying method yields the lowest water activity at 0.37 as a result of its reduced moisture content.
